<Link id="l00209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="209"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="210"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Compute the call-site table.  The entry for an invoke has a try-range</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="211"><Highlight kind="comment">/// containing the call, a non-zero landing pad, and an appropriate action.  The</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="212"><Highlight kind="comment">/// entry for an ordinary call has a try-range containing the call and zero for</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="213"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the landing pad and the action.  Calls marked &#39;nounwind&#39; have no entry and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="214"><Highlight kind="comment">/// must not be contained in the try-range of any entry - they form gaps in the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="215"><Highlight kind="comment">/// table.  Entries must be ordered by try-range address.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00216" /><CodeLine lineNumber="216"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00217" /><CodeLine lineNumber="217"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Call-sites are split into one or more call-site ranges associated with</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="218"><Highlight kind="comment">/// different sections of the function.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00219" /><CodeLine lineNumber="219"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00220" /><CodeLine lineNumber="220"><Highlight kind="comment">///   - Without -basic-block-sections, all call-sites are grouped into one</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00221" /><CodeLine lineNumber="221"><Highlight kind="comment">///     call-site-range corresponding to the function section.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00222" /><CodeLine lineNumber="222"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00223" /><CodeLine lineNumber="223"><Highlight kind="comment">///   - With -basic-block-sections, one call-site range is created for each</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00224" /><CodeLine lineNumber="224"><Highlight kind="comment">///     section, with its FragmentBeginLabel and FragmentEndLabel respectively</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00225" /><CodeLine lineNumber="225"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      set to the beginning and ending of the corresponding section and its</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00226" /><CodeLine lineNumber="226"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      ExceptionLabel set to the exception symbol dedicated for this section.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00227" /><CodeLine lineNumber="227"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      Later, one LSDA header will be emitted for each call-site range with its</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00228" /><CodeLine lineNumber="228"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      call-sites following. The action table and type info table will be</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00229" /><CodeLine lineNumber="229"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      shared across all ranges.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00230" /><CodeLine lineNumber="230" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ehstreamer/#a49694eb08442bb35020b9d8dfad6d7e5"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ehstreamer/#a49694eb08442bb35020b9d8dfad6d7e5">EHStreamer::computeCallSiteTable</a>(</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="358"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Emit landing pads and actions.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="359"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="360"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The general organization of the table is complex, but the basic concepts are</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00361" /><CodeLine lineNumber="361"><Highlight kind="comment">/// easy.  First there is a header which describes the location and organization</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00362" /><CodeLine lineNumber="362"><Highlight kind="comment">/// of the three components that follow.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00363" /><CodeLine lineNumber="363"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00364" /><CodeLine lineNumber="364"><Highlight kind="comment">///  1 The landing pad site information describes the range of code covered by</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00365" /><CodeLine lineNumber="365"><Highlight kind="comment">///     the try.  In our case it&#39;s an accumulation of the ranges covered by the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00366" /><CodeLine lineNumber="366"><Highlight kind="comment">///     invokes in the try.  There is also a reference to the landing pad that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00367" /><CodeLine lineNumber="367"><Highlight kind="comment">///     handles the exception once processed.  Finally an index into the actions</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00368" /><CodeLine lineNumber="368"><Highlight kind="comment">///     table.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00369" /><CodeLine lineNumber="369"><Highlight kind="comment">///  2 The action table, in our case, is composed of pairs of type IDs and next</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00370" /><CodeLine lineNumber="370"><Highlight kind="comment">///     action offset.  Starting with the action index from the landing pad</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00371" /><CodeLine lineNumber="371"><Highlight kind="comment">///     site, each type ID is checked for a match to the current exception.  If</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00372" /><CodeLine lineNumber="372"><Highlight kind="comment">///     it matches then the exception and type id are passed on to the landing</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00373" /><CodeLine lineNumber="373"><Highlight kind="comment">///     pad.  Otherwise the next action is looked up.  This chain is terminated</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00374" /><CodeLine lineNumber="374"><Highlight kind="comment">///     with a next action of zero.  If no type id is found then the frame is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00375" /><CodeLine lineNumber="375"><Highlight kind="comment">///     unwound and handling continues.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00376" /><CodeLine lineNumber="376"><Highlight kind="comment">///  3 Type ID table contains references to all the C++ typeinfo for all</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00377" /><CodeLine lineNumber="377"><Highlight kind="comment">///     catches in the function.  This tables is reverse indexed base 1</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00378" /><CodeLine lineNumber="378"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00379" /><CodeLine lineNumber="379"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Returns the starting symbol of an exception table.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00380" /><CodeLine lineNumber="380" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ehstreamer/#a420cc4a7a63b33a52659768b133b5f1b"><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcsymbol">MCSymbol</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ehstreamer/#a420cc4a7a63b33a52659768b133b5f1b">EHStreamer::emitExceptionTable</a>() &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00623" /><CodeLine lineNumber="623"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The call-site table is a list of all call sites that may throw an</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00629" /><CodeLine lineNumber="629"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The table begins with the number of bytes, stored as an LEB128</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00630" /><CodeLine lineNumber="630"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// compressed, unsigned integer. The records immediately follow the record</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00633" /><CodeLine lineNumber="633"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00634" /><CodeLine lineNumber="634"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   &#42; The position of the call-site.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00635" /><CodeLine lineNumber="635"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   &#42; The position of the landing pad.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00636" /><CodeLine lineNumber="636"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   &#42; The first action record for that call site.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00637" /><CodeLine lineNumber="637"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
